"\"To love our native country, and to study its be- nefit and its glory, to be interested in its concerns, is natural to all men, and is indeed our common duty. A poet makes a further step: for, endea. vouring to do Loneur to it, it is allowable in hiin even to be partial in its cause ; for he is not tied to truth, or fettered by the laws of history. Homer and Tassoare justly praised for choosing their heroes out of Greece and Italy: Virgil indeed made his"